descriptionMd:
I was invited by Daisy Alioto, CEO of Dirt Media, to do the design and development of their new brand Clone.
&nbsp;
I designed and engineered the website and backend CMS for a new brand and curated link aggregation site from [dirt.fyi](dirt.fyi) and Boys Club. We went for a web 1.0, classic feel, inspired by the original Yahoo! homepage and terminal-based bulletin boards. The CMS featured support for pulling in dynamic RSS feeds, a flow for syndicating those to the site with manual approval, and for collaborators to add new links manually in real time .The website features a visitor count and an interactive sheep cursor that also “clones” new sheep that hang out and jump around at the bottom of the page on the footer.
